8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 736, L.D. 1117, “An Act to Strengthen
10 Maine's Workforce Through Certified Preapprenticeship Training Programs”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 6 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 5 in L.D.) by
12 inserting after the following: "Council," the following: 'as considered appropriate and
13 permissible by the department,'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 6 in paragraph C in the last line (page 1, line
15 38 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "success" the following: ', either through the
16 use of funds provided under this subsection or through workforce funds provided by a
17 different source'
18 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
19 'Sec. 2. Department of Labor; study. The Department of Labor shall, within
20 existing resources, conduct a study reviewing certified preapprenticeship training programs
21 and registered apprenticeship programs in the State and in other states. The study must
22 include an analysis of the programs reviewed, including but not limited to the funding
23 methods of the programs. The department shall invite relevant stakeholders to participate
24 in the study. The department shall report its findings, including any suggested legislation,
25 to the Joint Standing Committee on Labor by December 3, 2025. The joint standing
26 committee may report out a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature
27 based on the report.'
28 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
29 number to read consecutively.
30 SUMMARY
3311 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, clarifies that the Maine
3322 Apprenticeship Program may consult on funding matters with the Maine Apprenticeship
3333 Council as the Department of Labor considers appropriate and permissible. The
3344 amendment also provides that at least 51% of funding provided by the Maine
3355 Apprenticeship Program must be given to certified preapprenticeship training programs
